job.description:
Are you passionate about testing and troubleshooting? Do you thrive in a dynamic environment and enjoy working on complex assignments?
If so, we have the perfect opportunity for you!
We are looking for
Software Engineer Developer in Test (SEDT)
to join our pan-Baltic agile team. You’ll play a key role in ensuring high-quality deliveries for mission critical account services used by thousands of our customers.
In Swedbank you have the opportunity to:
Collaborate with a      cross-functional Accounts Baltic team across Lithuania, Latvia, and      Estonia;
Develop and maintain various      account and deposit services, ensuring high-quality software delivery;
Ensure secure and efficient      payment transactions within Swedbank and across the EU and global markets;
Continuously improve and refine      software development and maintenance processes;
Deliver high-value solutions to      customers and users with speed, quality, and stability;
Navigate complex areas of accounts      services, learning and adapting to new challenges daily.
What is needed in this role:
Software quality assurance is the area you enjoy and feel      comfortable with;
Knowledge      of QA methodologies, software development processes, and testing      frameworks;
Experience with automation tools and frameworks;
A collaborative, open-minded team player who is willing to learn      on the go;
Familiarity with Agile (Scrum, SAFe) ways of working;
Fluent English and at least one Baltic language.
Our daily tech stack:
Java · REST · SpringBoot · Kafka · IntelliJ · Git · Jenkins · Selenium · Postman · JMeter · Oracle DB · MS SQL · Jira · Confluence · MS Teams
With us, you can experience:
Personal and professional growth through self-leadership and continuous development;
Meaningful work that positively impacts our workplace, our customers, and society;
An open and collaborative culture that encourages cross-functional teamwork and provides networking opportunities;
A supportive and inclusive environment that promotes a balanced and sustainable work-life, with flexible working conditions when suitable for the role;
Benefits such as our share based reward program Eken, company pension plan, employee offer for banking products, health insurance.
" Join our team and...
you’ll collaborate with talented, driven colleagues who are committed to delivering high-quality, stable software — and who go the extra mile to  improve how we work. Needless to mention fun, friendly atmosphere and plenty of opportunities for your growth development."
Migle Nael, your future leader
We look forward to your application at 28.12.2025 the latest.
We may begin the selection during the application period, so we welcome your application as soon as possible.
We have made our choice regarding recruitment media and therefore kindly decline contact with ad sellers or sellers of other recruitment services.
If you are to be employed in Latvia, please note that the salary offered for this position ranges from 3
,200–4,800 €
gross i.e. before taxes. Read more here.
If you are to be employed in Lithuania, please note that the salary offered for this position ranges from 3
,900–5,800 €
gross i.e. before taxes. Read more here.
If you are to be employed in Estonia, please note that the salary offered for this position ranges from 3
,650–5,450 €
gross i.e. before taxes. Read more here!
Swedbank does not discriminate anybody based on gender, age, sexual orientation or sexual identity, ethnicity, religion or disability – everybody is welcome.
